Hey all. We wanted to let everyone know what we are focusing on right now. We're experimenting with how to be more transparent with where we're headed. 

Here's the plan: we're going to make an issue for each area of focus which contain actionable tasks, plus this issue as an overview into those focus areas. All these tickets will have the [milestone label](https://github.com/atom/atom/issues?labels=milestone). So at any time you want to see where we are, just check out the issues in that milestone label.

We currently have three main initiatives:
- [x] Make the react editor the default editor https://github.com/atom/atom/pull/2423
- [x] Basic, better windows support for developers https://github.com/atom/atom/issues/2447
- [ ] Issues and PRs

We will be focusing on these initiatives, so issues and PRs relating to them will likely receive more attention from us.

The third initiative is a little vague, but it is an ongoing effort. It is comprised of our everyday work:
- Fixing or responding to issues
- Merging or responding to PRs
- Coming up with ways to be more efficient at issue triage
### A bit about the team

So you have an idea of who is working on atom at GitHub

